     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="5"/>
   <head>To his friend the Author on his Fancies Theater.</head>
   <l>
      <hi>FAncie,</hi> in all his <hi>Colours</hi> ne're appear'd</l>
   <l>So variously delightfull, as in this</l>
   <l>Magnificent <hi>Theater,</hi> which thou hast rear'd</l>
   <l>Out of thy <hi>Genuine braine,</hi> and call'st it <hi>His.</hi>
   </l>
   <l>Here does he take all shapes, and act all parts;</l>
   <l>The noble <hi>Hero,</hi> and the humble <hi>Swaine</hi>;</l>
   <l>The jocund Lovers, and lamenting hearts.</l>
   <l>As well the Buskind, as the Comick straine.</l>
   <l>Fancie has something here for every one,</l>
   <l>From <hi>Reveller</hi> to <hi>Mourner</hi>; still provided,</l>
   <l>Each brings a proper apprehension;</l>
   <l>And one not by anothers humor guided.</l>
   <l>But let all come and welcome: The severe</l>
   <l>
      <hi>Cato</hi> himselfe may have free entrance here.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>R. Broome.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
